reviewText: The 29th century sends a ship back in time to destroy Voyager because they are convinced that Voyager will be the cause of millions of deaths.  The attempt to destroy Voyager fails and they end up in Earth's 20th century.  They must find a way to stop a man on earth from sending up a space shuttle that will be the catalyst for a casuality loop. It's a good time travel two part series.  Don't want to spoil the whole thing by telling it all.
